for the interaction between the inner shell and valence electrons. The values
obtained at the SCF approximation level from a set of gaussian valence orbitals
contracted in double-zeta form and enriched with polarization functions compare
well with experimental assignments of force and interaction constants, as well as
integrated intensities from infrared data. The transferability of atomic force
fields and polar tensors (second derivatives of total energies and first derivatives
of dipole moments with respect to atomic displacements in cartesian coordinates)
is discussed.},
Doi = {10.1080/00268978000100761}
}


